INSTALLING THE INTERPRETER:
----------------------------

0. DOWNLOAD "heist_main.cpp", "heist_cpp_interop.hpp", 
   & THE "heist_interpreter_headers" FOLDER

1. FIND THE "HEIST_DIRECTORY_FILE_PATH" MACRO (COMMENTED
   OUT) IN "heist_main.cpp" & UNCOMMENT IT

2. COPY THE FILEPATH YOU DOWNLOADED FILES TO IN STEP #0 AS A
   STRING TO THE "HEIST_DIRECTORY_FILE_PATH" MACRO IN STEP #1

3. COMPILE THE INTERPRETER: $ clang++ -std=c++17 -O3 -o heist_main heist_main.cpp
    i) FLAG DESCRIPTIONS:
       a. "-std=c++17": [REQUIRED] compile using the C++17 standard
       b. "-O3": [RECOMMENDED FOR FASTEST EXECUTION] maximum optimization
                 -> longest compile time, but fastest runtime
       c. "-Os": [RECOMMENDED FOR MOST BUILDS] optimizes for binary's size
                 -> faster compile-time than -O3, smaller binary, & close runtime
   ii) ON COMPILE TIME:
       a. Full -O3 compilation takes about 30s. Be patient. Compilation
          time has been traded for FAST runtime.
       b. -Os compilation takes about 20s. Generated binary is smaller than
          -O3's (as expected) & its runtime is nearly as fast





SETTING UP BETTER COMMAND-LINE INTERFACE -- FOR BASH & ZSH:
------------------------------------------------------------

0. BASH: OPEN ~/.bash_aliases (OR ~/.bashrc)
0. ZSH: OPEN ~/.zshrc

1. WRITE: alias heist='<FILEPATH-FROM-STEP-#0-IN-"INSTALLING THE INTERPRETER"-HERE>/heist_main'

2. SAVE THE FILE, CLOSE THE CURRENT TERMINAL WINDOW, & RELAUNCH THE TERMINAL

2. NOW, WRITING "heist" FROM ANYWHERE IN THE TERMINAL LAUNCHES THE INTERPRETER!





SETTING UP A BUILD SYSTEM -- FOR SUBLIME TEXT:
-----------------------------------------------

0. GOTO "Tools > Build System > New Build System"

1. WRITE:
    {
      "cmd": ["<FILEPATH-FROM-STEP-#0-IN-"INSTALLING THE INTERPRETER"-HERE>/heist_main", "-nansi", "-script", "$file"],
      "file_regex": "^(..[^:]*):([0-9]+):?([0-9]+)?:? (.*)$",
    }

2. SAVE THE FILE AS "Heist-Scheme.sublime-build"

3. NOW THE HEIST SCHEME INTERPRETER OUGHT TO APPEAR IN "Tools > Build System"
